heading: What proportion of young Europeans are graduates?
subheading: In 2022, more than 40% of people aged 25-34 in the EU27 had completed higher education. The EU target for tertiary education is 45% by 2030.
tooltip1: of 25-34 aged with tertiary educational attainment
textNote: Tertiary education i.e. education provided by universities and other higher education institutions.
